# Lottero TypeScript backend standards

- **Architecture/layering**: `controller -> service -> repository`. Controllers validate inputs + map exceptions to HTTP; services contain business rules; repositories only do SQL/DB access.
- **DI pattern**: Use `tsyringe` with `@injectable()` classes, constructor injection, and `private readonly` deps. Prefer `export default class X` (one class per file).
- **Error handling**: Only throw `BaseException` subclasses (`ValidationException`, `NotFoundException`, `ConflictException`, …). Controllers must `catch` and `error.report(res)` when `error instanceof BaseException`; otherwise return `500`. Controllers will only validate the existence of the properties. Business-logic will be validated by the service.
- **Controller style**: Use arrow properties (`public foo = async (...) => {}`) to preserve `this`. Don’t leak raw DB errors/messages to clients.
- **DB safety**: Always use parameter placeholders (`$1`, `$2`, …) for values. Never string-interpolate user input into SQL. If dynamic identifiers are unavoidable, strictly whitelist/quote them. The database schema will be in `@/src/database/schema.sql`.
- **Types**: Avoid `any`. Use explicit `Promise<T>` return types on public methods. Use request-body models for routes (`req: Request<..., BodyType>`).
- **Nullish checks**: Prefer `x == null` (covers `null|undefined`) or explicit checks; avoid truthiness for numeric IDs/booleans.
- **Formatting**: Double quotes, trailing commas in multi-line literals/params, and consistent naming (`*_id` for DB fields; `camelCase` in TS).

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ Controller error handling
try {
  /* ... */
} catch (error) {
  if (!(error instanceof BaseException))
    return res.status(500).json({ message: "An error has occured" });
  error.report(res);
}
```

```ts
// ✅ Repository query
await pool.query('SELECT * FROM "groups" WHERE id = $1', [id]);
```
